cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM 

This paper presents a method for monocular model-based 3D tracking, which involves computer vision and robotics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a technique for optimization, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely category as well. The method also involves refining the object pose, which is related to robotics and control, making cs.RO (Robotics) another possible category. The paper also compares its method with state-of-the-art methods, which involves performance evaluation and machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with videos, which involves multimedia and computer graphics, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category as well.
